      <intermediateExchange id="0f82e67e-f2fc-5ba7-b6a2-0a091d64f2d3" unitId="487df68b-4994-4027-8fdc-a4dc298257b7" amount="4.24648149596718E-05" intermediateExchangeId="4c2b1cc3-84e5-4e35-b74e-8815eadbc674" activityLinkId="db6536db-5f07-5bf0-9179-7419a6157c5a">
        <name xml:lang="en">[sulfonyl]urea-compound</name>
        <unitName xml:lang="en">kg</unitName>
        <comment xml:lang="en">This exchange is an aggregate of proxies for applied pesticide(s) Chlorimuron, Fomesafen, Fomesafen Sodium, Sulfentrazone, Thifensulfuron, Tribenuron (2.018E-3 kg/ha {1,2,1,1,1}; 2.983E-2 kg/ha {1,4,1,1,1}; 7.086E-2 kg/ha {1,2,1,1,1}; 5.494E-2 kg/ha {1,4,1,1,1}; 1.373E-3 kg/ha {1,2,1,1,1}; 2.036E-3 kg/ha {1,2,1,1,1}, respectively).
Average over state-wide reported cropped area of soybean for all tillage practices (CTIC 2020a) and across all rotation patterns (Socolar et al 2021 ) - calculated from specified herbicide/insecticide/fungicide quantity applied to treated acres weighted by share of acres treated with that herbicide/insecticide/fungicide (2015,2017,2018,2020-USDA NASS data,  USDA NASS 2021e).
Sources:
