      <intermediateExchange id="b37e7d6d-92bf-512e-8590-cbe0ed747be0" unitId="86bbe475-8a8f-44d8-914c-e398787e7121" amount="0.000101893209542534" intermediateExchangeId="7225e2a6-7fd6-40e2-b341-f097b027d119" activityLinkId="c9e6a57e-3ae0-57ed-9914-50f1def85f20">
        <name xml:lang="en">application of plant protection product, by field sprayer</name>
        <unitName xml:lang="en">ha</unitName>
        <comment xml:lang="en">0.3865 ha/ha (1.02E-4 ha/kg soybean) market for application of plant protection product, by sprayer
The dataset has an effective number of passes for application of pesticides of 0.39 ha: 1.07 applications of herbicides on 17.6% of cropped area, 1.04 applications of insecticides on 9.5% of cropped area, 1.06 applications of fungicides on 9.4% of cropped area (USDA NASS 2021e). Application by sprayer accounts for 76% (0.30passes) and aircraft for 24% (0.09 passes). The budgets for soybean in Iowa do not provide information for aerial pesticide application as an individual operation.  However, aerial application is in common use in Iowa. An aerial pesticide application rate of  24% has been estimated from custom rate surveys for contracted farm operations (Plastina A and Johanns A 2021; Plastina, Johanns, Massman 2020; Plastina, Johanns, Wynne 2019; Plastina, Johanns, Welter 2018; Plastina A and Johanns A (2021) Iowa Farm Custom Rate Survey, 2021 (2018, 2019, 2020). Cooperative Extension Service, Iowa State University of Science and Technology. https://www.extension.iastate.edu/agdm/crops/pdf/a3-10.pdf ; Plastina, Johanns, Massman (2020) 2020 Iowa Farm Custom Rate Survey File A3-10. Cooperative Extension Service, Iowa State University of Science and Technology. https://iastate.app.box.com/embed/s/hbsel0lckc7vle74v4jkg7mf0ph3z39s/file/630724245464 ; Plastina, Johanns, Wynne (2019) 2019 Iowa Farm Custom Rate Survey File A3-10. Cooperative Extension Service, Iowa State University of Science and Technology. https://www.extension.iastate.edu/monroe/sites/www.extension.iastate.edu/files/monroe/2019%20Custom%20Rate%20Survey.pdf ; Plastina, Johanns, Welter (2018) 2018 Iowa Farm Custom Rate Survey File A3-10. Cooperative Extension Service, Iowa State University of Science and Technology. https://www.extension.iastate.edu/hancock/sites/www.extension.iastate.edu/files/hancock/2018_CustomRateSurvey.pdf ).
Because aerial application is almost universally contracted service, it is most often not included in crop-specific enterprise budgets as a separate line item, instead being included under "custom" or "miscellaneous". Consequently, this dataset uses  the ratio of custom farm rate survey responses for aerial application to the total respondents to provide a state crop level average estimate of aerial applications.  This value covers all farmers responding and does not distinguish among crops. The Iowa Custom Rate Surveys, cited most widely in farm economics projections lacking the state's own Survey, average 24% 2018-2021 (Plastina A and Johanns A 2021, 2020, 2019, 2018).  The National Agricultural Aviation Association's estimates that approximately 28% of all US cropland (excluding range, pasture, and forest lands) is treated by aircraft annually (NAAA 2019, NAAA 2020).
Field operations are as identified in crop- and rotation-specific enterprise crop budgets supplied by the regional agricultural extension office and matched to equipment type in the budget or crop guidance.  (ISU Extension 2021; ISU Extension 2020a; ISU Extension 2020b; ISU Extension 2020c; ISU Extension 2020d).  Operations are matched to equipment type and where multiple options are available, the share of each is determined from guidance and annual farmer survey data (Custom Rate Summaries) for contracted operations/equipment.Where an operation applies only to a portion of the harvested area, the number of passes has been scaled by the % of harvested area to which it applies (e.g., manure spreading or insecticide) as indicated by USDA statistics (applications) or USDA reports (manure use) or as otherwise indicated in enterprise crop budgets.
Source(s): 
Plastina A and Johanns A (2021) Iowa Farm Custom Rate Survey, 2021 (2018, 2019, 2020). Cooperative Extension Service, Iowa State University of Science and Technology. https://www.extension.iastate.edu/agdm/crops/pdf/a3-10.pdf ; Plastina, Johanns, Massman (2020) 2020 Iowa Farm Custom Rate Survey File A3-10. Cooperative Extension Service, Iowa State University of Science and Technology. https://iastate.app.box.com/embed/s/hbsel0lckc7vle74v4jkg7mf0ph3z39s/file/630724245464 ; Plastina, Johanns, Wynne (2019) 2019 Iowa Farm Custom Rate Survey File A3-10. Cooperative Extension Service, Iowa State University of Science and Technology. https://www.extension.iastate.edu/monroe/sites/www.extension.iastate.edu/files/monroe/2019%20Custom%20Rate%20Survey.pdf ; Plastina, Johanns, Welter (2018) 2018 Iowa Farm Custom Rate Survey File A3-10. Cooperative Extension Service, Iowa State University of Science and Technology. https://www.extension.iastate.edu/hancock/sites/www.extension.iastate.edu/files/hancock/2018_CustomRateSurvey.pdf ; Nemecek T, Bengoa X, Lansche J, et al  (2015) Methodological Guidelines for the Life Cycle Inventory of Agricultural Products, Version 3.0. 84.. .  ; Nemecek T. &amp; Kägi T. (2007) Life Cycle Inventories of Swiss and European Agricultural Production Systems. Final report ecoinvent V2.0 No. 15a. Agroscope Reckenholz-Taenikon Research Station ART, Swiss Centre for Life Cycle Inventories, Zurich and Dübendorf, Switzerland, retrieved from: www.ecoinvent.ch. .  ; ISU Extension (2021) Crop Production Costs Budgets - tabulated. Cooperative Extension Service, Iowa State University of Science and Technology. https://www.extension.iastate.edu/agdm/crops/pdf/a1-20.pdf ; ISU Extension (2020) Crop Production Costs Budget - Soybeans following Corn. Cooperative Extension Service, Iowa State University of Science and Technology. https://www.extension.iastate.edu/agdm/crops/xls/a1-20cfs_tbl2.xlsx ; ISU Extension (2020) Crop Production Costs Budget - Soybeans following Corn. Cooperative Extension Service, Iowa State University of Science and Technology. https://www.extension.iastate.edu/agdm/crops/xls/a1-20cfs_tbl2.xlsx ; ISU Extension (2020) Crop Production Costs Budget - Low-till soybeans following corn. Cooperative Extension Service, Iowa State University of Science and Technology. https://www.extension.iastate.edu/agdm/crops/xls/a1-20lowtillsfctbl6.xlsx ; ISU Extension (2020) Crop Production Costs Budget - Strip Till Herbicide Tolerant Drilled Soybeans Following Corn (no till Soybean). Cooperative Extension Service, Iowa State University of Science and Technology. https://www.extension.iastate.edu/agdm/crops/xls/a1-20striptillsfctbl5.xlsx</comment>
