      <intermediateExchange id="0459887e-82e7-518c-b3fe-56f0dae73a52" unitId="86bbe475-8a8f-44d8-914c-e398787e7121" amount="0.000220755106209395" intermediateExchangeId="75168394-3da2-467a-90a1-285836ccd00d" activityLinkId="ce3b617c-7d3c-5df2-9a64-0e9554f11941">
        <name xml:lang="en">fertilising, by broadcaster</name>
        <unitName xml:lang="en">ha</unitName>
        <comment xml:lang="en">0.8373 ha/ha (2.21E-4 ha/kg soybean) fertilising, by broadcaster
The dataset has an effective number of passes for application of mineral fertilisers (NPKS) of 0.88: 1.13 N applications on 15.5% of cropped area, 1.03 P applications on 26.3% of cropped area, 1.00 K applications on 34.3% of cropped area, and 1.10 S applications on 8.7% of cropped area (USDA NASS 2021e, NPKS data from 2015, 2017, 2018, 2020). Applications of N are split between anhydrous ammonia and other NPK fertilisers because they are generally applied differently, with different equipment. Anhydrous ammonia application (knifing/injection) is calculated as market share of N that is anhydrous ammonia * total N applications. Other N application is then: total USDA N applications less applications of anhydrous ammoni.  (here, 25.21%). Thus, the dataset includes 0.13 anhydrous ammonia applications via injection (0.25 * 15.5% of crop area with applied N) and 0.84 other fertiliser applications via broadcast.

Field operations are as identified in crop- and rotation-specific enterprise crop budgets supplied by the regional agricultural extension office and matched to equipment type in the budget or crop guidance.  (ISU Extension 2021; ISU Extension 2020a; ISU Extension 2020b; ISU Extension 2020c; ISU Extension 2020d).  Operations are matched to equipment type and where multiple options are available, the share of each is determined from guidance and annual farmer survey data (Custom Rate Summaries) for contracted operations/equipment. Where an operation applies only to a portion of the harvested area, the number of passes has been scaled by the % of harvested area to which it applies (e.g., manure spreading or insecticide) as indicated by USDA statistics (applications) or USDA reports (manure use) or as otherwise indicated in enterprise crop budgets.
Source(s): 
USDA NASS (2021) SOYBEAN- APPLICATIONS, MEASURED IN LB / ACRE / YEAR, AVG (fertilizer and pesticides, amount, number of applications) - 2000-2021. US Department of Agriculture (USDA) National Agricultural Statistics Service. https://quickstats.nass.usda.gov (direct query: https://quickstats.nass.usda.gov/results/1D738304-38A8-3977-B7BA-B67A7AF33530) ; ISU Extension (2021) Crop Production Costs Budgets - tabulated. Cooperative Extension Service, Iowa State University of Science and Technology. https://www.extension.iastate.edu/agdm/crops/pdf/a1-20.pdf ; ISU Extension (2020) Crop Production Costs Budget - Soybeans following Corn. Cooperative Extension Service, Iowa State University of Science and Technology. https://www.extension.iastate.edu/agdm/crops/xls/a1-20cfs_tbl2.xlsx ; ISU Extension (2020) Crop Production Costs Budget - Soybeans following Corn. Cooperative Extension Service, Iowa State University of Science and Technology. https://www.extension.iastate.edu/agdm/crops/xls/a1-20cfs_tbl2.xlsx ; ISU Extension (2020) Crop Production Costs Budget - Low-till soybeans following corn. Cooperative Extension Service, Iowa State University of Science and Technology. https://www.extension.iastate.edu/agdm/crops/xls/a1-20lowtillsfctbl6.xlsx ; ISU Extension (2020) Crop Production Costs Budget - Strip Till Herbicide Tolerant Drilled Soybeans Following Corn (no till Soybean). Cooperative Extension Service, Iowa State University of Science and Technology. https://www.extension.iastate.edu/agdm/crops/xls/a1-20striptillsfctbl5.xlsx</comment>
