      <intermediateExchange id="8aad2914-f587-5988-8b7c-5a5d7ad06fd7" unitId="487df68b-4994-4027-8fdc-a4dc298257b7" amount="0.0759570153483244" intermediateExchangeId="6c50f204-1e98-422e-b20c-70088087f505" activityLinkId="d56098af-2e8c-50ad-8682-419f001ff07d">
        <name xml:lang="en">manure, liquid, swine</name>
        <unitName xml:lang="en">kg</unitName>
        <comment xml:lang="en">The total effective manure application rate of 653 kg/ha (0.172 kg/kg soybean) is calculated from USDA ERS data for amount of manure applied (12.8 kg/ha; 0.17 kg/kg soybean) on share of crop area treated (5.1%)  (years available: 2002, 2006) USDA ARMS 2015. The manure data has significant uncertainty due to both the age of the available data and the statistical limitations imposed by confidentiality for USDA survey respondents.
About 40% of applied manure is in liquid form, calculated from the share of dry, semi-dry and slurry and lagoon manure applied  from ARMS data. USDA describes the liquid/slurry and dry manure shares as "Statistically unreliable due to a low sample size" (USDA ARMS 2015a). 55.9% of manure from cattle. 44.1% of manure from swine. Applied swine manure is assumed to be liquid only. USDA data shows zero share from poultry manure. Cattle manure is apportioned between solid and liquid consistent with USDA estimated shares after accounting for swine manure
The calculated solid and liquid manure shares in this dataset are thus 44.1% solid and 55.9% liquid manure.  Volume of liquid manure is calculated using density ~8.4lb/gal (8-9 lb/gal). Total mass liquid manure is 7.6E-2 kg/kg soybean, total volume of liquid manure is 7.55E-5 m3/kg soybean.
Sources:
Beegle D and Peters J. (2019) Common Manure Test Results Conversions. National Cooperative Extension Resource, Livestock And Poultry Environmental Learning Community (Lpelc). https://lpelc.org/common-manure-test-results-conversions/ accessed October 5, 2021 USDA ARMS (2015) Agricultural Resource Management Survey (ARMS) Farm Financial and Crop Production Practices: Manure Table, Corn. USDA. https://data.ers.usda.gov/reports.aspx?ID=17883</comment>
