      <intermediateExchange id="e09f1b22-302a-59ac-8ab7-7d747fded78c" unitId="487df68b-4994-4027-8fdc-a4dc298257b7" casNumber="007722-76-1" amount="7.4672300513503E-05" intermediateExchangeId="d1567df0-6921-5a69-adb0-71cacf11683c" activityLinkId="af317044-6689-57af-bf74-129120fc4910">
        <name xml:lang="en">monoammonium phosphate</name>
        <unitName xml:lang="en">kg</unitName>
        <comment xml:lang="en">7.47E-5 kg monoammonium phosphate/kg soybean 
Quantities of specific fertiliser are calculated based on US fertiliser market share and nutrient compositions from IFA data to meet total nutrient demand N-P-K-S: 0.5--4.55--11.94--0.12 kg/ha  (USDA NASS data for  2015, 2017, 2018, 2020), over reported cropped area of specified crop (includes all rotation patterns):  quantity of N applied to treated acres times percent of planted soy bean acres treated (USDA NASS) times share of N supplied by compound in U.S. consumption mix (ecoinvent and IFA 2019) times mass compound per mass N in compound.
Sources: 
USDA NASS (2021) SOYBEAN- APPLICATIONS, MEASURED IN LB / ACRE / YEAR, AVG (fertilizer and pesticides, amount, number of applications) - 2000-2021. US Department of Agriculture (USDA) National Agricultural Statistics Service. https://quickstats.nass.usda.gov (direct query: https://quickstats.nass.usda.gov/results/1D738304-38A8-3977-B7BA-B67A7AF33530) ; Ecoinvent U.S. consumption mix for N fertilisers, from IFA data; IFA (2021) Nutrient content in percentage - IFA Fertilizer Converter. International Fertilizer Association. https://www.ifastat.org/converter/fertilizer-converter/ accessed 2021-06-24</comment>
