      <intermediateExchange id="a42757ec-6465-5f6e-aedf-6aacd245637e" unitId="487df68b-4994-4027-8fdc-a4dc298257b7" casNumber="007447-40-7" amount="0.000114118450678395" intermediateExchangeId="f9c6e4e7-e45c-423e-b48e-f7e140efb38e" activityLinkId="d24990e6-efed-56f6-9de3-d91a67feae4e">
        <name xml:lang="en">potassium chloride</name>
        <unitName xml:lang="en">kg</unitName>
        <comment xml:lang="en">1.14E-4 kg potassium chloride/kg soybean 
Quantities of specific fertiliser are calculated based on US fertiliser market share and nutrient compositions from IFA data to meet total nutrient demand N-P-K-S: 0.5--4.55--11.94--0.12 kg/ha  (USDA NASS data for  2015, 2017, 2018, 2020). Quantity of specific fertiliser calculated from: average total N application (2010, 2014, 2016, 2018) reported cropped area of specified crop (includes all rotation patterns) and share of fertilisers in U.S. consumption mix (ecoinvent and IFA 2019) times each fertiliser's K2O to N ratio (IFA), subtracted from the application rate for the necessary nutrient, and multiplied by the mass of the compound over the mass of K2O in the compound.
Sources: 
USDA NASS (2021) SOYBEAN- APPLICATIONS, MEASURED IN LB / ACRE / YEAR, AVG (fertilizer and pesticides, amount, number of applications) - 2000-2021. US Department of Agriculture (USDA) National Agricultural Statistics Service. https://quickstats.nass.usda.gov (direct query: https://quickstats.nass.usda.gov/results/1D738304-38A8-3977-B7BA-B67A7AF33530) ; Ecoinvent U.S. consumption mix for N fertilisers, from IFA data; IFA (2021) Nutrient content in percentage - IFA Fertilizer Converter. International Fertilizer Association. https://www.ifastat.org/converter/fertilizer-converter/ accessed 2021-06-24</comment>
