      <intermediateExchange id="90167771-4dbf-54f4-8b2d-a6a33ed9c1b5" unitId="487df68b-4994-4027-8fdc-a4dc298257b7" casNumber="007778-80-5" amount="0.0061270250397869" intermediateExchangeId="db8488c0-a49f-4550-8bae-f2356ce1de64" activityLinkId="9e15cedb-cd06-50ce-bb85-abc4562b2a9a">
        <name xml:lang="en">potassium sulfate</name>
        <unitName xml:lang="en">kg</unitName>
        <comment xml:lang="en">6.13E-3 kg potassium sulfate/kg soybean 
Quantities of specific fertiliser are calculated based on US fertiliser market share and nutrient compositions from IFA data to meet total nutrient demand N-P-K-S: 0.5--4.55--11.94--0.12 kg/ha  (USDA NASS data for  2015, 2017, 2018, 2020). Quantity of specific fertiliser calculated from: average total N application (2010, 2014, 2016, 2018) reported cropped area of specified crop (includes all rotation patterns) and share of fertilisers in U.S. consumption mix (ecoinvent and IFA 2019) times each fertiliser's K2O to N ratio (IFA), subtracted from the application rate for the necessary nutrient, and multiplied by the mass of the compound over the mass of K2O in the compound. The K2O and S demands remaining after meeting the N demand using the US fertilizer mix (ecoinvent, IFA 2019) are met from a mix of ammonium sulfate, potassium nitrate, potassium chloride, and potassium sulfate, the quantities of which are determined by satisfying the demand without exceeding other nutrient demands by more than 1%, and any S demand remaining is met using elemental sulfur. 
Sources: 
USDA NASS (2021) SOYBEAN- APPLICATIONS, MEASURED IN LB / ACRE / YEAR, AVG (fertilizer and pesticides, amount, number of applications) - 2000-2021. US Department of Agriculture (USDA) National Agricultural Statistics Service. https://quickstats.nass.usda.gov (direct query: https://quickstats.nass.usda.gov/results/1D738304-38A8-3977-B7BA-B67A7AF33530) ; Ecoinvent U.S. consumption mix for N fertilisers, from IFA data; IFA (2021) Nutrient content in percentage - IFA Fertilizer Converter. International Fertilizer Association. https://www.ifastat.org/converter/fertilizer-converter/ accessed 2021-06-24</comment>
