        <name xml:lang="en">soybean seed, for sowing</name>
        <unitName xml:lang="en">kg</unitName>
        <comment xml:lang="en">Each planted hectare uses 49.27 kg seed (1.3E-2 kg/kg soybean). This value is calculated from a seeding rate of 326,179 seeds/ha (Licht M 2020a; Casteel S, Smith R 2022) and an average seed count of 6,621 seeds/kg (averaged from Geyer A, Hankinson M, McCormic J, and Lindsey L 2021, Plansek T 2021). About 95% of planted soybean is genetically engineered for herbicide tolerance (USDA NASS 2022).  Germination of 90.0% and stand losses are accounted for in the seeding rate (Beals S 2020; Knox S et al 2019; Staton M, Chilvers M, Tiedje C. 2022) Sources:
Licht M (2020) "Updated views on corn and soybean planting recommendations" 4/1/20 10:43. Cooperative Extension Service, Iowa State University of Science and Technology. https://crops.extension.iastate.edu/blog/mark-licht/updated-views-corn-and-soybean-planting-recommendations , Casteel S, Smith R (2022) Economic Optimal Seed Rates Of Soybean. Soybean Extension Specialist. Purdue UniversityPurdue University. https://extension.entm.purdue.edu/newsletters/pestandcrop/article/economic-optimal-seed-rates-of-soybean/ , USDA NASS. (2020). Crops/Stocks Survey (or Agricultural Survey) for the years 2000-20 - Recent Trends in GE Adoption. US Department of Agriculture (USDA). https://www.ers.usda.gov/data-products/adoption-of-genetically-engineered-crops-in-the-us/documentation/ , Langemeier MR, Nielsen B, Vyn TJ, Casteel S, and Johnson B (2021) 2021 Purdue Crop Cost &amp; Return Guide. Purdue Extension Publ. ID-166-W. Purdue Extension - University of Indiana. https://ag.purdue.edu/commercialag/home/resource/2021/12/2022-crop-cost-and-return-guide/ [URL accessed Jan 2022], Beals S (2020) Seed Quality Update. Illinois crop improvement association-Seed Lab Report. https://www.ilcrop.com/illinois-seed-news/seed-lab-report/seed-quality-update/ ; Knox S et al (2019) Soybean Seed Germination Concerns. University of Nebraska–Lincoln Extension, Institute of Agriculture and Natural Resources. https://cropwatch.unl.edu/2019/soybean-seed-germination-concerns ; Staton M, Chilvers M, Tiedje C. (2022) Seed Quality Considerations. Michigan State University Extension. https://www.canr.msu.edu/news/soybean_seed_quality_considerations#:~:text=While%20much%20of%20the%20soybean,and%20it%20is%20always%20conservative. ;Geyer A, Hankinson M, McCormic J, and Lindsey L (2021) 2021 OHIO SOYBEAN PERFORMANCE TRIALS. Ohio State University Extension and OARDC. https://ohiocroptest.cfaes.osu.edu/soy2020/ ;Plansek T (2021) Beyer, Corteva in 'two-dog battle' over U.S. soy market. Reuters. April 9, 2021. . https://www.reuters.com/article/us-usa-soybeans-seeds-focus/bayer-corteva-in-two-dog-battle-over-u-s-soy-market-idUSKBN2BW1IE Accessed May 23, 2022., Mekonnen et al (2018) Water, Energy, and Carbon Footprints of Bioethanol from the U.S. and Brazil. Environ. Sci. Technol. 52:14508–14518. Mesfin M. Mekonnen, Thiago L. Romanelli, Chittaranjan Ray, Arjen Y. Hoekstra, Adam J. Liska, and Christopher M.U. Neale. https://pubs.acs.org/doi/10.1021/acs.est.8b03359</comment>
