        <comment xml:lang="en">3.53E-5 ha/kg tillage, cultivating, chiselling (0.134 effective pass(es) per year). 
Field operations are as identified in crop- and rotation-specific enterprise crop budgets supplied by the regional agricultural extension office and matched to equipment type in the budget or crop guidance. Operations are matched to equipment type and where multiple options are available, the share of each is determined from guidance and annual farmer survey data (Custom Rate Summaries) for contracted operations/equipment. Field cultivation and tillage operations are specific to the tillage regime used. Soybean is  47% reduced till, 39% no till, and 13% conventional till in Iowa (CTIC 2020a).This operation applies only to conventionally tilled fields. 
Sources:
