Field operations are as identified in crop- and rotation-specific enterprise crop budgets supplied by the regional agricultural extension office and matched to equipment type in the budget or crop guidance. Operations are matched to equipment type and where multiple options are available, the share of each is determined from guidance and annual farmer survey data (Custom Rate Summaries) for contracted operations/equipment. Field cultivation and tillage operations are specific to the tillage regime used. Soybean is  47% reduced till, 39% no till, and 13% conventional till in Iowa (CTIC 2020a).This operation applies to fields under all tillage regimes. 
Sources:
ISU Extension (2021) Crop Production Costs Budgets - tabulated. Cooperative Extension Service, Iowa State University of Science and Technology. https://www.extension.iastate.edu/agdm/crops/pdf/a1-20.pdf , ISU Extension (2020) Crop Production Costs Budget - Soybeans following Corn. Cooperative Extension Service, Iowa State University of Science and Technology. https://www.extension.iastate.edu/agdm/crops/xls/a1-20cfs_tbl2.xlsx , ISU Extension (2020) Crop Production Costs Budget - Soybeans following Corn. Cooperative Extension Service, Iowa State University of Science and Technology. https://www.extension.iastate.edu/agdm/crops/xls/a1-20cfs_tbl2.xlsx , ISU Extension (2020) Crop Production Costs Budget - Low-till soybeans following corn. Cooperative Extension Service, Iowa State University of Science and Technology. https://www.extension.iastate.edu/agdm/crops/xls/a1-20lowtillsfctbl6.xlsx , ISU Extension (2020) Crop Production Costs Budget - Strip Till Herbicide Tolerant Drilled Soybeans Following Corn (no till Soybean). Cooperative Extension Service, Iowa State University of Science and Technology. https://www.extension.iastate.edu/agdm/crops/xls/a1-20striptillsfctbl5.xlsx , ISU Extension (2020) Budgets and other resources from IA Extension. Cooperative Extension Service, Iowa State University of Science and Technology. https://www.extension.iastate.edu/agdm/cdcostsreturns.html ; CTIC (2020a) OpTIS - Operational Tillage Information System. Conservation Technology Information Center (CTIC). https://www.ctic.org/optis_tabular_query accessed March 23, 2021</comment>
