      <elementaryExchange id="ed860cf5-bbe9-50eb-8cc6-a8ca306e5512" unitId="487df68b-4994-4027-8fdc-a4dc298257b7" casNumber="007664-41-7" amount="0.000410734613943133" elementaryExchangeId="0f440cc0-0f74-446d-99d6-8ff0e97a2444" formula="H3N">
        <name xml:lang="en">Ammonia</name>
        <unitName xml:lang="en">kg</unitName>
        <comment xml:lang="en">Ammonia volatilised from applied mineral and organic fertilisers, 1.6 kg NH3/ha (4.11E-4kg NH3/kg soybean) total, 0.0 kg NH3/ha (4.11E-4 kg NH3/kg soybean) from synthetic fertilisers, 1.5 kg NH3/ha (3.99E-4 kg NH3/kg soybean) from manure. NH3 from volatilisation of mineral fertilisers is calculated using Tier 2 emission factors (temperate climate, specific fertiliser) from the European Environment Agency, EMEP/EEA 3Da1, Table3.2 (EEA 2019). NH3 from manure application is calculated with emission factors provided in EMEP/EEA 3.D.a.2.a (Animal manure applied to soils) (EEA 2019) for manure types used as (fraction TAN in total N)*(EF manure spreading per TAN) for each animal group and type. (kg NH3-N/kg N applied: cattle, solid: 0.474; swine, liquid: 0.242). The emissions from manure calculated here do not account for the change in N mineralization and phosphate runoff with incorporation type or time. Where impacts from manure application are expected to be significant, this should be considered as N volatilisation during and after application of manure ranges from as low as 1% N with direct injection to ~5% with immediate incorporation to 20-40% without incorporation (Sawyer J, Mallarino A P (2016) Using Manure Nutrients for Crop Production. Cooperative Extension Service, Iowa State University of Science and Technology. https://store.extension.iastate.edu/product/12874 and Midwast Plan Services MWPS-18, 3ed)..</comment>
        <uncertainty>
          <lognormal meanValue="0.000410734613943133" mu="-7.797563260194901" variance="0.008" varianceWithPedigreeUncertainty="0.0172"/>
          <pedigreeMatrix reliability="2" completeness="3" temporalCorrelation="4" geographicalCorrelation="1" furtherTechnologyCorrelation="1"/>
        </uncertainty>
        <synonym xml:lang="en">azane</synonym>
        <property propertyId="f2283db2-62e4-467f-b9ac-c4f45be563b4" amount="0.0" isDefiningValue="false" isCalculatedAmount="false" unitId="487df68b-4994-4027-8fdc-a4dc298257b7">
