      <elementaryExchange id="d5bdf47f-c83e-5380-b654-e00d22e14cc1" unitId="487df68b-4994-4027-8fdc-a4dc298257b7" casNumber="000124-38-9" amount="3.41233416175485E-05" elementaryExchangeId="aa7cac3a-3625-41d4-bc54-33e2cf11ec46" formula="CO2">
        <name xml:lang="en">Carbon dioxide, fossil</name>
        <unitName xml:lang="en">kg</unitName>
        <comment xml:lang="en">CO2 emissions from use of urea fertilisers and lime, 1.29E-1 kg/ha (3.41E-5 kg/kg soybean): 1.294E-1 kg/ha from urea and urea ammonium nitrate; 0.E+0 kg/ha from lime. 
Emissions are calculated following the IPCC NIR Guidelines, §11.3 and §11.4, using IPCC NIR equations 11.12 (lime) and 11.13 (urea) (mass of lime/urea * emissions factor for lime/urea) with Tier 1 emissions factors (IPCC 2006b).  EF limestone = 0.12 kg CO2-C/kg limestone (0.06-0.12, uniform) and EF urea = 0.2 kg CO2-C/kg urea (0.1-0.2, uniform) applied to both urea and the approximately 35% of UAN that is urea. The result is converted from kg CO2-C to kg CO2 (multiplying by the molar mass of CO2/mass of C in CO2 = 44.01/12)</comment>
        <uncertainty>
          <lognormal meanValue="3.41233416175485E-05" mu="-10.285528902927993" variance="0.0" varianceWithPedigreeUncertainty="0.0092"/>
          <pedigreeMatrix reliability="2" completeness="3" temporalCorrelation="4" geographicalCorrelation="1" furtherTechnologyCorrelation="1"/>
        </uncertainty>
        <synonym xml:lang="en">Carbon dioxide</synonym>
