      <elementaryExchange id="609afb26-4c2a-585d-9f28-b7c5eaace946" unitId="487df68b-4994-4027-8fdc-a4dc298257b7" casNumber="014265-44-2" amount="3.69264046744786E-05" elementaryExchangeId="329fc7d8-4011-4327-84e4-34ff76f0e42d" formula="O4P-3">
        <name xml:lang="en">Phosphate</name>
        <unitName xml:lang="en">kg</unitName>
        <comment xml:lang="en">Phosphate leaching to ground water 0.14 kg PO4/ha (3.693E-5 kg/kg soybean): 7.006E-2 kg PO4/ha from manure and 7.E-2 kg PO4/ha from leaching from arable land.  Phosphate leaching to ground water is calculated using the SALCA-P model (Prasuhn 2006) with an average leaching factor for arable lands and the amount of phosphate in any applied manure, as implemented in the ecoinvent agricultural LCI tool (see Ecoinvent_Too_Model_Description_20191015.pdf). Does not incorporate state or county data on soils, slope or conservation drainage infrastructure. Calculated with the ecoinvent agricultural LCI tool.</comment>
