        <comment xml:lang="en">Land occupation per year (annual growing season).  Land is under rotation with other annual crop production (~80% corn-soy, ~20% corn-corn, Socolar et al 2021 ). US NRCS data indicates that total cropland in Iowa has expanded 3% over the last 20 years, met entirely by land idled under the Conservation Reserve Program (CRP) (NRCS 2020a), resulting in a flux to/from annual crop that is essentially steady state. 
